## Typography Standards
- **Headings**: Playfair Display (serif)
- **Body Text**: Montserrat (sans-serif)
- **Font Weights**: 400 (regular), 600 (semibold), 700 (bold)

## Code Style Guidelines

### TypeScript
- Always use TypeScript strict mode
- Define interfaces for all props and data structures
- Avoid `any` type - use `unknown` or proper types
- Use const assertions for constant objects
- Prefer type inference when obvious

### React Components
- Use functional components with TypeScript
- Prefer named exports for components
- Use React.FC for component typing when props include children
- Keep components under 300 lines - split if larger
- Co-locate related components and types

### File Naming Conventions
- Components: PascalCase (e.g., `HeroSection.tsx`)
- Utilities: camelCase (e.g., `utils.ts`)
- Constants: camelCase file, UPPER_SNAKE_CASE for exports
- Pages: lowercase with hyphens (e.g., `[slug]/page.tsx`)

### Component Structure
```typescript
// 1. Imports (external, then internal)
import React from 'react';
import { motion } from 'framer-motion';
import { Button } from '@/components/ui/Button';

// 2. Types/Interfaces
interface ComponentProps {
  title: string;
  // ...
}

// 3. Constants (if any)
const ANIMATION_DURATION = 0.3;

// 4. Component
export const Component = ({ title }: ComponentProps) => {
  // Hooks first
  // Event handlers
  // Render
  return <div>{title}</div>;
};
```

### Styling Guidelines
- Use Tailwind utility classes first
- Create custom utilities in `globals.css` for repeated patterns
- Follow mobile-first responsive design
- Use Tailwind's custom color names (coastal-cream, accent-burgundy)
- Maintain consistent spacing scale (4, 8, 12, 16, 24, 32, 48, 64)

### Animation Standards
- Use Framer Motion for complex animations
- Transition duration: 300-400ms for hover effects
- Use `ease-in-out` or custom easing for smooth animations
- Implement scroll-triggered animations with Intersection Observer
- Keep animations subtle and purposeful

### Image Optimization
- Always use Next.js Image component
- Provide width and height props
- Use `priority` for above-the-fold images
- Use `loading="lazy"` for below-the-fold images
- Provide descriptive alt text for accessibility

### Accessibility Requirements
- Maintain WCAG AA color contrast minimum
- Include ARIA labels for interactive elements
- Ensure keyboard navigation works
- Add visible focus states
- Use semantic HTML elements

## Key Features Implementation

### Loading Overlay
- Display on initial page load only
- Minimum 1.5s display time
- Fade-in/fade-out animations
- Logo centered on coastal gradient background

### Booking Bar
- Hidden on page load
- Appears after 300px scroll
- Fixed to top with backdrop-blur
- Inline date pickers (not modals)
- Mobile: Collapsible with floating button

### Performance Standards
- Lighthouse score: 90+ on all metrics
- Initial JS bundle: <200KB
- First Contentful Paint: <1.5s
- Time to Interactive: <3.5s

## API Integration Patterns
- Use Next.js API routes for server-side logic
- Implement proper error handling with try-catch
- Return consistent response formats
- Add loading states for all async operations
- Implement optimistic updates where appropriate

## Testing Guidelines
- Test responsive behavior at all breakpoints
- Verify accessibility with keyboard navigation
- Check loading states and error states
- Test form validations
- Verify image lazy loading

## Git Commit Conventions
```
feat: Add new feature
fix: Bug fix
style: Formatting changes
refactor: Code restructuring
docs: Documentation updates
perf: Performance improvements
test: Test additions/updates
```

## Don't Do This
- ❌ Never use inline styles (use Tailwind classes)
- ❌ Don't create example/placeholder code
- ❌ Don't run dev servers (assume they're running)
- ❌ Don't use `any` type in TypeScript
- ❌ Don't hardcode content that should be in constants
- ❌ Don't skip alt text on images
- ❌ Don't use harsh black shadows (use warm tones)

## Do This
- ✅ Use semantic HTML elements
- ✅ Implement proper TypeScript types
- ✅ Follow the established color palette
- ✅ Add hover states to all interactive elements
- ✅ Optimize images and implement lazy loading
- ✅ Maintain consistent spacing and typography
- ✅ Test on mobile and desktop viewports
- ✅ Write clean, maintainable code

## Folder Structure
```
/app - Next.js pages (App Router)
/components
  /layout - Header, Footer, BookingBar, LoadingOverlay
  /sections - Page sections (Hero, Welcome, Testimonials, etc.)
  /ui - Reusable UI components (Button, Card, Input, etc.)
/lib - Utilities and constants
/public/images - Static assets
```

